{{Orphan|date=April 2016}}

'''PCaaS''' or, ''Personal Computer as a Service'', is a Personal Computer hardware and optionally software leasing, licensing and delivery model in which personal computer and optionally software (particularly installed on the PC) are leased and licensed on a [[subscription business model|subscription basis]]. The subscription often includes services such as staging, imaging, maintenance, fix, logistics services and may also be bundled with helpdesk services, data [[backup]] and recovery.

There are several vendors that have PCaaS offerings including, [http://www.bizbang.biz Bizbang], [https://www.dell.com/en-us/work/shop/pc-as-a-service-for-business/cp/pcaas Dell], [http://www8.hp.com/us/en/services/daas.html HP] (they call theirs Device as a Service), and [http://www.thinkfwd.com.au/documents/PCaaS_From_Lenovo.pdf Lenovo] (in Australia only for now).

