'''Wevolver''' provides access to high quality engineering projects, to help people develop better technology.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/open-source-hardware-makerlab-wired-nextgen|title=Why hardware needs to go open source|first=Nicole|last=Kobie|publisher=Wired Magazine}}</ref> Their stated mission is to "enable anyone, anywhere to develop hardware that improves life." <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wevolver.com/about|title=Wevolver - Develop Perfect Hardware Together|website=www.wevolver.com}}</ref> Wevolver 1.0 was a project repository for strictly [[Open Source]] projects, but in 2.0, it has been expanded to include a version control system, and is available for use by private teams in addition to open source projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makezine.com/2017/10/16/open-world-wevolvers-cameron-norris/|title=Open World: Wevolver's Cameron Norris - Make:|last=Grace-Flood|first=Liam|date=16 October 2017|website=|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

Among the projects using their version control system are [[OpenROV]], [[Plen]], [[exiii]] hackberry, and [[InMoov]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/2015/feb/06/robots-for-good-hospitalised-children-superpowers|title=Meet the robot giving hospitalised children superpowers|last=Spinks|first=Rosie|date=2015-02-06|website=the Guardian|access-date=2018-01-17}}</ref>

In interviews, Wevolver team members have said the strongest part of their platform is their community, with over 300k followers on [[instagram]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/wevolverapp/|title=Wevolver.com (@wevolverapp) • Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-17}}</ref> three news blogs, and myriad hosted projects, they've said the most important part of any [[Open-source model|Open-source]] platform is the people using it.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://makezine.com/2017/10/16/open-world-wevolvers-cameron-norris/|title=Open World: Wevolver's Cameron Norris {{!}} Make:|date=2017-10-16|work=Make: DIY Projects and Ideas for Makers|access-date=2018-01-17|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/cameron-norris/tech-for-good-robots_b_10061910.html|title=You Don't Need to Be an Engineer to Build 'Robots for Good'|date=2016-05-26|work=HuffPost UK|access-date=2018-01-17|language=en-GB}}</ref>

