{{DISPLAYTITLE:Inspired Education Group}} {{notability|1=Companies|date=February 2019}}
{{Infobox company | name = Inspired Education Group | logo = File:Inspired Logo.png | type = Private | industry = Education | founded = 2013 | hq_location = London, Milan, Auckland, Bogota, Johannesburg,and Dubai. | area_served = Europe, the Middle East, Africa, Australia and Latin America. | website = https://inspirededu.com/ }}
'''Inspired Education Group''' is a group who operates and builds schools in [[Europe]], the [[Middle East]], [[Africa]], [[Australia]] and [[Latin America]].
== History == Inspired was founded by Nadim M Nsouli in 2013<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://oakleycapitalinvestments.com/portfolio-companies/inspired/|title=Inspired {{!}} Oakley Capital Investments|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref>, when his group acquired Reddam House in [[South Africa]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com/south-africa/business-day/20150930/282179354895615|title=Group Opens Flagship School in UK|last=|first=|date=|website=Business Day|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref> Since its founding, Reddam House has acquired and built 9 schools in South Africa, along with the group's flagship school, [[Reddam House, Berkshire|Reddam House Berkshire]], in [[Wokingham|Wokingham, England]]. The school grounds in Wokingham were taken over from [[Bearwood College]], in 2015.<ref name=":0" />
Nsouli - the founder, [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] and [[Chairman]] - has worked as a lawyer and as an investment banker, and he has led the group since its founding.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.gulf-insider.com/british-school-bahrain-gets-inspired/|title=The British School of Bahrain gets inspired|last=gulfinsider|first=|date=2018-02-11|website=Gulf Insider|language=en-US|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref> Inspired’s President is Graeme Crawford, a South African educator and founder of [[Reddam House]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/education/hsc-results-2016-rise-of-reddam-house-20161214-gtan1k.html|title=HSC results 2016: Rise of Reddam House|last=|first=|date=|website=The Sydney Morning Herald|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref> [[Stephen Spurr|Dr Stephen Spurr]] is the Group Education Director and was the Head Master of [[Westminster School]] in London from 2004 to 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/10-ways-to-enrich-your-childs-science-education-f5rqdjgznxt|title=10 ways to enrich your child’s science education|last=|first=|date=2012-01-25|work=The Times|access-date=2019-01-21|language=en|issn=0140-0460}}</ref> He joined Inspired in 2014<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inspirededu.com/meet-the-team/|title=Inspired - Meet the Team|last=|first=|date=|website=inspirededu.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref>
The group’s strategy has been described as "''buy and build''",<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ta.com/portfolio/investments/inspired|title=Inspired {{!}} Consumer Sector {{!}} TA {{!}} A Private Equity Firm|website=TA Associates|language=en|access-date=2019-01-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.educasinternational.com/investments|title=Investments : EDUCAS, an education investment firm|website=www.educasinternational.com|access-date=2019-01-04}}</ref> involving the purchase of existing schools, as well as the building of new schools. It has offices in [[London]], [[Milan]], [[Auckland]], [[Bogotá|Bogota]], [[Johannesburg]],and [[Dubai]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inspirededu.com/contact--us/|title=CONTACT US|last=|first=|date=|website=inspirededu.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref>
Schools in other European countries that form part of the Inspired group include [[St George's School in Switzerland|St. George's International School]] in [[Switzerland]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://stgeorges.ch/|title=St. George's {{!}} International School in Montreux Switzerland|last=|first=|date=|website=stgeorges.ch|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21|quote=St. George's International School is a proud member of Inspired, a leading global premium schools group operating...}}</ref> [[St. John's International School (Belgium)|St. John's International School]] in [[Belgium]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.brusselstimes.com/brussels/6710/st-john-s-international-school-in-brussels-joins-the-inspired-network|title=The Brussels Times - St John’s International School in Brussels joins the “Inspired Network”|last=SU|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2019-01-21|language=en-gb}}</ref> St. Louis School in [[Italy]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.educationinvestor.co.uk/(X(1)A(zUvzX4La1AEkAAAAM2IzNTg4NmUtZWJkMS00M2I0LTk5YWYtM2NmMTg3MTBkYWVj256nVE9BtsBq5ilXIF0t3EX83dY1)S(y0wf1a55iqkqe155yu3w1522))/showarticle.aspx?ID=5606&AspxAutoDetectCookieSupport=1|title=EducationInvestor - Article: Italy: Inspired invests in two Italian schools|last=|first=|date=|website=www.educationinvestor.co.uk|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref> and Sotogrande International School in [[Spain]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sis.ac/|title=Sotogrande International School|last=|first=|date=|website=Sotogrande International School|language=en-GB|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref> In the [[Middle East]], the group has acquired [[British School of Bahrain]].<ref name=":1" /> Inspired's [[Latin America|Latin American]] schools include Blue Valley School in [[Costa Rica]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nacion.com/economia/negocios/inspired-group-invertira-2-millones-en-centro/44G5CJ4AMZD5NI24XSQ7GRIVZI/story/|title=Inspired Group invertirá $2 millones en centro educativo costarricense Blue Valley|last=|first=|date=|website=La Nación, Grupo Nación|language=es-LA|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref> Colegio San Mateo in [[Colombia]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://losmejorescolegios.com/colegio/colegio-san-mateo-apostol/|title=Colegio San Mateo Apóstol (Bogotá)|last=|first=|date=|website=Los Mejores Colegios de Colombia|language=es-ES|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref> and Cambridge College Lima in [[Peru]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thepienews.com/news/inspired-acquires-cambridge-college-lima/|title=Inspired international schools group acquires Cambridge College Lima|last=News|first=The PIE|date=|website=thepienews.com|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref> By 2017, Inspired operated more than 30 schools<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/eqt-credit-completes-financing-to-leading-premium-school-group-inspired-1013145932|title=EQT Credit Completes Financing to Leading Premium School Group Inspired {{!}} Markets Insider|last=GmbH|first=finanzen net|date=|website=markets.businessinsider.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref>, and as of 2018 educating over 35,000 students in 46 schools.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inspirededu.com/our-schools/|title=Inspired Schools - Premium Private Education|last=|first=|date=|website=inspirededu.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-21}}</ref>
Inspired acquired part of New Zealand’s biggest private-education provider [[ACG Education]]’s schools division in 2018 from [[Pacific Equity Partners]] for about $500 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=a0af9550-2fd2-11e9-8a48-314bc9b7e8f1&url=L25ld3MvYXJ0aWNsZXMvMjAxOC0wOS0yMC9pbnNwaXJlZC1zY2hvb2xzLWlzLXNhaWQtdG8tbmVhci1hY3F1aXNpdGlvbi1vZi1hY2ctc2Nob29scy11bml0|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2019-02-13}}</ref>
